Beijing Lecture On Sino-Japanese Relations
BEIJING , November 19 ( Xinhua ) -- At a lecture today held by the China Institute for International Strategic Studies , former Chinese ambassador to Japan Xu Dunxin said that President Jiang Zemin 's upcoming visit to Japan is the first by a Chinese head of state and has far-reaching historical significance .
At his key-note speech on the occasion of the 20th anniversary of of the signing of the Sino-Japanese Treaty of Peace and Friendship , Xu discussed future developments of Sino-Japanese ties with some senior diplomats , retired generals and scholars .
Some participants agreed that the Sino-Japanese relationship is the most important bilateral relationship in the Asia-Pacific region , and that the smooth development of bilateral relations is not only in the fundamental interests of people of the two countries but also in the interest of peace and development in the rest of the world .
